:"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Hampden","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Great or Little Hampden (Bucks)."],"variants":[{"name":"Hamden","meanings":["English (Kent and Berkshire): habitational name from Hamden in Smarden, Kent, or from Great or Little Hampden in Buckinghamshire."]}]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Robert de Hampden was born about 1099, in Buckinghamshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Baldwin de Hampden, was 29 and his mother, Mrs. Baldwin de Hampden, was 25. He had at least 1 son. He died in England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"Abt 1099–":"umbes 1099–Surnud","1099–Male":"1099–Surnud","1130–1147":"1130–1147","1072–Male":"1072–Surnud","1075–Female":"1075–Surnud","Abt 1097":"umbes 1097","1147":"1147","Abt 1099":"umbes 1099","1099":"1099","1075":"1075","1130":"1130","1072":"1072","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hampden, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1099–":"noin 1099–Kuollut","1099–Male":"1099–Kuollut","1130–1147":"1130–1147","1072–Male":"1072–Kuollut","1075–Female":"1075–Kuollut","Abt 1097":"noin 1097","1147":"1147","Abt 1099":"noin 1099","1099":"1099","1075":"1075","1130":"1130","1072":"1072","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","England":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Hampden, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1099–":"environ 1099–Décédé","1099–Male":"1099–Décédé","1130–1147":"1130–1147","1072–Male":"1072–Décédé","1075–Female":"1075–Décédée","Abt 1097":"environ 1097","1147":"1147","Abt 1099":"environ 1099","1099":"1099","1075":"1075","1130":"1130","1072":"1072","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Hampden, Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Robert de Hampden est né environ 1099, à Buckinghamshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Baldwin de Hampden, avait 29 ans et sa mère, Mrs. Baldwin de Hampden, avait 25 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils. Il est décédé à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni."},"de":{"Abt 1099–":"um 1099–Verstorben","1099–Male":"1099–Verstorben","1130–1147":"1